{"closingIssuesReferences":[],"files":[{"path":"resources/products/token-spy/PHASE1-ARCHITECTURE.md","additions":8,"deletions":4,"changeType":"MODIFIED"},{"path":"resources/products/token-spy/PRODUCT-SCOPE.md","additions":4,"deletions":0,"changeType":"MODIFIED"},{"path":"resources/products/token-spy/README.md","additions":11,"deletions":5,"changeType":"MODIFIED"}],"reviewDecision":"REVIEW_REQUIRED","reviewRequests":[],"reviews":[{"id":"PRR_kwDORMI4oM72b1RZ","author":{"login":"Lightheartdevs"},"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","body":"Core fix is right. Three audit findings addressed cleanly:\n\n**Token Spy auth (High):** verified the new `_get_upstream_auth_headers()` behavior:\n- Strips client `authorization` from forwarded headers in both Anthropic and OpenAI endpoints.\n- Injects server-side `UPSTREAM_API_KEY` with correct scheme (`x-api-key` for Anthropic, `Bearer` for OpenAI).\n- **Fails closed with 503** when `UPSTREAM_API_KEY` is unset and upstream is not local. Correct security posture.\n- `_uses_local_upstream()` guard allows local self-hosted upstreams to run without provider auth — good ergonomics.\n\n**Windows docs + incubator disclaimers:** content is accurate.\n\n**Merge-conflict warning:** this PR overlaps with #973 (approved) and #966 (open). All three rewrite `WINDOWS-QUICKSTART.md` / `SUPPORT-MATRIX.md`. Since this one carries a security-relevant payload, I'd merge it first and force #966/#973 to rebase.\n\nApproving on the condition that the merge is coordinated — don't let the doc overlap delay the Token Spy fix.","submittedAt":"2026-04-18T14:05:16Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"reactionGroups":[],"state":"DISMISSED","commit":{"oid":"9aff088fe4a9f8f106463d8b013931e6ff2ecafb"}}],"statusCheckRollup":[{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-18T15:34:24Z","conclusion":"FAILURE","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24607953291/job/71957256131","name":"integration-smoke","startedAt":"2026-04-18T15:34:13Z","statu